    {
      "id": "intro_2",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "The sculptor speaks",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 2.76,
      "endTime": 10.94
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "What do you have to be able to do to appreciate sculpture?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 10.95,
      "endTime": 17.34,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "What",
            "label": "疑问词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "What",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "什么"
          },
          {
            "word": "You",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "你，你们"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Appreciation of sculpture depends upon the ability to respond to form in 3 dimensions.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 17.35,
      "endTime": 25.68
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "That is perhaps why sculpture has been described as the most difficult of all arts;",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 25.69,
      "endTime": 32.09,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "That",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "certainly it is more difficult than the arts which involve appreciation of flat forms, shape in only two dimensions.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 32.1,
      "endTime": 41.9,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          },
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Many more people are 'form-blind' than colour-blind.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 41.91,
      "endTime": 48.45,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "are",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The child learning to see, first distinguishes only two-dimensional shape; it cannot judge distances, depths.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 48.46,
      "endTime": 57.87,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Later, for its personal safety and practical needs, it has to develop (partly by means of touch) the ability to judge roughly 3-dimensonal distances.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 57.88,
      "endTime": 71.8,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "But having satisfied the requirements of practical necessity, most people go no further.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 71.81,
      "endTime": 78.93
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Though they may attain considerable accuracy in the perception of flat form,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 78.94,
      "endTime": 84.98,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "may",
            "label": "情态动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "they do not make the further intellectual and emotional effort needed to comprehend form in its full spatial existence.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 84.99,
      "endTime": 95.22,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Not",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "不，不是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "This is what the sculptor must do.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 95.23,
      "endTime": 98.03,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "This",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          },
          {
            "text": "what",
            "label": "疑问词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "This",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "这，这个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "What",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "什么"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "He must strive continually to think of and use, form in its full spatial completeness.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 98.04,
      "endTime": 106.87,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "He gets the solid shape as it were, inside his head--he thinks of it, whatever its size, as if he were holding it completely enclosed in the hollow of his hand.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 106.88,
      "endTime": 120.69,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          },
          {
            "text": "his",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          },
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          },
          {
            "text": "his",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "He mentally visualizes a complex form from all round itself;",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 120.7,
      "endTime": 127.29
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "he knows while he looks at one side what the other side is like; he identifies himself with its centre of gravity, its mass, its weight;",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 127.3,
      "endTime": 138.33,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "what",
            "label": "疑问词"
          },
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          },
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          },
          {
            "word": "What",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "什么"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "he realizes its volume as the space that the shape displaces in the air.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 138.34,
      "endTime": 144.8,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Air",
            "pos": "n.",
            "meaning": "空格"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "And the sensitive observer of sculpture must also learn to feel shape simply as shape, not as description or reminiscence.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 144.81,
      "endTime": 154.46,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Not",
            "pos": "adv.",
            "meaning": "不，不是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "He must, for example, perceive an egg as a simple single solid shape quite apart from its significance as food,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 154.47,
      "endTime": 164.42,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s17",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "or from the literary idea that it will become a bird.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 164.43,
      "endTime": 169.07,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s18",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "And so with solids such as a shell, a nut, a plum, a pear, a tadpole, a mushroom,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 169.08,
      "endTime": 178.08
    },
    {
      "id": "s19",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "a mountain peak, a kidney, a carrot, a tree-trunk, a bird, a bud, a lark, a ladybird, a bulrush, a bone.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 178.09,
      "endTime": 191.27
    },
    {
      "id": "s20",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "From these he can go on to appreciate more complex forms or combinations of several forms.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 191.28,
      "endTime": 196.28,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "can",
            "label": "情态动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    }
  ]
